column16: C 300 4MATIC is available as PZEV, FFV and ULEV versions for MY 2014. Litmus Test requires 3-Cycle method (M5C) for PZEV, Derived 5-Cycle (D5C) for FFV and Vehicle Specific 5-Cycle (V5C) for ULEV versions. Mercedes has selected to use the appropriate Litmus FE calculation method defined for each test group.UPDATE 10/08/2014: Relabel due to EPA confirmatory testing (C/D).

C 300 4MATIC is available as PZEV and FFV version in MY 2014. Litmus Test requires 3 Cycle method for the PZEV version while the FFV version can be labeled using derived 5 Cycle method. Mercedes has chosen not to use the 3-cycle method for both test groups. UPDATE 10/08/2014: Relabel due to EPA confirmatory testing (C/D).
